# ========================================
#
# 1. NEVER commit .env to version control
# 2. Use different keys for development/staging/production
# 3. Rotate keys regularly (monthly recommended)
# 4. Use read-only keys when possible
# 5. Restrict key permissions in provider dashboards
# 6. Monitor key usage for anomalies
#
# For production:
# - Use environment variables in hosting platform
# - Never hardcode secrets in application code
# - Consider using secret management (AWS Secrets Manager, Vault)
# - Upgrade to Standard tier for production deployments
#
# ========================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# ========================================
#
# "Environment variables not loading"
# → Restart your development server
# → Check file is named exactly .env (not .env.txt)
# → Verify file is in project root
# → Check for syntax errors (no spaces around =)
#
# "Still seeing example values"
# → You're using .env.example directly
# → Copy to .env and fill real values
#
# "Application can't find variables"
# → Check variable names match exactly
# → Verify you're loading from correct .env file
# → Review your framework's env loading docs
